HEADWORD: Indo-Germanic
<hw>In`do-Ger*man"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Indo-</ets> + <ets>Germanic</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Same as <er>Aryan</er>, and
<er>Indo-European</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pertaining to or denoting the Teutonic family of
languages as related to the Sanskrit, or derived from the ancient Aryan
language.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indoin</ent>⟦br⟧
